Description: Fragment of strap handle of a Knidian pottery transport amphora. Clay medium-fine light brown; light grey core. Rectangular stamp.
Type series: KT1102 (Virginia Grace's unpublished K(nidian) T(ype) series)
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 200, 41 Name Nysios.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0279)
